bio:
NYC
Poetry & Prose by @dejaraee  
My newest book ‘Come Home to Yourself’ is now available🦋

social_posts.post_text: Come home to yourself 💓 link in bio
A liberating realization 💓
Take a deep breath. Everything is going to be okay. Please don’t get too ahead of yourself. Settle into the present moment. This universe will take care of you 🌼
Now replace “You” with “I” and read it back to yourself. As many times as it takes until you wholeheartedly believe it.
A reminder for you 🤍 book link in bio :)

There doesn’t need to be any bitterness or hostility if someone chooses to leave your life. There is an abundance of new relationships and connections waiting for you. Allow people to float freely and move forward with the trust that everything is working towards the greater good.

Do not force relationships. Allow people to show you who they really are through their actions. And then decide whether that works for you. Stop begging people to change. Stop waiting around hoping someone will finally show up. Move on, move forward, let go. You are in control.
Let go of the things that are no longer serving you and move forward with faith that the right things are on their way 🦋
An excerpt from my newest book ‘Come Home to Yourself’ ❤️ link in bio
Slow down, breathe, look around. The point of your life is to enjoy it. 🦋
Temporary connections can be beautiful if you allow them to be what they are.
Be intentional with your energy 🦋
If he doesn’t want you — that is not a reflection of your worth. I promise you, the right people will eventually find you 🧡
Finding love in simplicity 🦋
Be intentional with your time and energy
🦋💓✨ I only love from my greatest capacity
Do not be disheartened by the people who can’t love you, who can’t truly see you. Passion is the most beautiful thing in this world. You deserve someone who can meet you in your depth.
The more we pour into ourselves, the more we can give to others. Link in bio 💓
Have patience with yourself. There is no rush in healing and growth 🦋

image_entities.entity: never again will i shrink my capacity to love
for someone that does not have the capacity to love me.

social_posts.post_text: Never, never again. Now repeat it to yourself, over and over again.
Find joy from within and that joy will dwell in you everywhere you go
The details define the truth. The details will tell you everything you need to know.
Trust yourself. Trust your intuition. It’s guiding you toward what is destined for you.
A perpetual cycle of hurting, learning and growing 🌱
A liberating realization. Nothing is ever as personal as it feels.

I know how discouraging long periods of loneliness can be. I understand the pain of perpetual disappointment. But please, don’t lose faith. Brighter seasons are coming, better people are coming. Everything in life is temporary.
Not everyone has the capacity for true intimacy. Save your energy for those who can reciprocate your level of love.
Be intentional with your time and energy.
I hope this reaches whoever needs to hear it 🦋

If you’ve walked away from a person or situation, yet continue to talk about it and obsess over it, your energy is still stuck in the past. If you want to move forward, you must let it all go. Stop trying to justify it or rationalize it — stop looking for answers. Leave the pieces on the floor and shift your focus to something else. You must continually and repeatedly do this if you want to truly move on.
Don’t settle for anything less than you deserve 💓
A reminder to always choose yourself. Check in with yourself. Question your intentions and decisions. You will thank yourself years from now.
Never again 🦋
Now repeat these to yourself and believe them wholeheartedly 🤍
True connection should feel easy and abundant. If you’re constantly questioning how someone feels about you, that may be a sign that it’s time to let go. 💓
Love is a feeling AND an action.
Energy going into the new year. I pray for an abundance of blessings & breakthrough for you 🦋

In this new year I urge you all to let go of the people and things that are no longer serving you. Let go of inconsistency, let go of control, let go of the past. And as you do this, you will witness your life transform into a beautiful reflection of everything you truly desire.
Be selective with your time, your energy, and your attention.
Release & enjoy. Let go & be still. Be open & relax. Slow down and enjoy the beautiful connections in your life. 💓
Be open and be free. You will always have yourself and that will always be enough. 💓
One of my favorite pieces from my first book ‘ebb & flow’

Yes, chemistry is important. Yes, a healthy & balanced relationship has both chemistry AND good character. However, many of us get disillusioned when choosing our life partners. We feel an intense spark, a magnetic attraction, and we are immediately willing to commit to this person without first understanding their true character. Eventually, we become disappointed because we realize that this person doesn’t have the capacity to show up for us in the ways we need. 

If you want to feel supported throughout life, if you want to truly feel like you have a life partner, you must look deeply at someone’s character. You must look past the surface and understand their morals and values, and who they are at the core of their being. 

Even if it takes some time, even if it requires loads of patience, I promise you — it will be worth it in the end.
Mantra for 2023. The hard things build the foundation for the good things to grow. 🌱
Regardless of how lost you may get, you can and will always find the way back to yourself.
It will come. Everything will turn out okay. You don’t need to worry so much. You don’t need to fear the future. Relax. Enjoy this moment. Enjoy this season. You have it for a reason.
Choose yourself now and you will thank yourself later 💛
A reminder for all those who need it. If you’re seeing this, it was meant to find you.
Allow your intuition to guide you 🧡

True love with challenge you to grow into your highest self. It will mirror back your negative coping mechanisms, and gently nudge you to create healthier thought patterns. True love isn’t always easy, but it’s always worth it.
A piece from my newest book ‘Come Home to Yourself’ link in bio 🤍
Spend less time comparing & more time creating 🤍

You don’t deserve to go your whole life wondering how someone feels about you. You don’t deserve to question whether the feelings are reciprocated. I promise you — balanced, healthy, all-encompassing love does exist. You just have to be willing to wait for it.
Gently let go of the people who are letting go of you 🦋
Let it all go 🦋
A soft Sunday reminder
Trust the process. One day it will all make sense.
You can and will find someone who is absolutely sure about you. You just need to have patience with the process and refuse to settle for anything less.
A piece from my newest book ‘Come Home to Yourself’ 💓 link in bio
A reminder to not take things so personally. Live lightly my friend, lightly.
Listen to your inner-knowing. Trust your intuition. You know what you truly want.
A piece from ‘Come Home to Yourself’ 🧡

A piece from my newest book ‘Come Home to Yourself’ 
Link in bio 💓
Stop wasting your time on people who don’t have the capacity to reciprocate your shine. The right people will find you when you let the wrong ones go.
This is your reminder to enjoy your life. The world is moving around you. Wake up and step into it.

When an anxious thought arises — put it down & let it go. Gently acknowledge it, and remind yourself that your anxiety does not reflect truth. Counter your ‘worst case scenarios’ with best case scenarios. Challenge your doubting thoughts and beliefs with positive thoughts and beliefs. And then gently move forward. Repeat this process as many times as needed.  With time, the more you do this, the easier it will become. Your anxiety will feel weaker, less convincing, and will hold much less power over you.
Appreciate people for the time that you have them. And if they leave, let them go with love. 💓
Have patience with the process. Appreciate the journey. This is your reminder that you do not need to rush through life. Everything will come in divine timing.
Let go & be free 🦋
If you’re seeing this — it’s for you 🧚‍♂️
Listen to your intuition. It will lead you towards where you’re meant to go 🦋
Beautiful people will come and go. Release your grip and let life flow 🦋
Put your trust in divine timing and watch as things fall perfectly into place.
Spend your energy on the things that truly matter. Spend your energy on the things that give you energy back.
Love is abundant 🦋
I promise you — they do exist. They are out there somewhere in the world waiting for you. Don’t lose hope, my friends.
Find peace in your presence. Find solace in your solitude. And the rest will unfold 🧚‍♂️

Happy Valentine’s Day, my friends ❤️‍🔥 Express gratitude to all the people who light a fire in your heart, who make you feel safe, who make you feel seen. Express gratitude for the relationship you have with yourself. Express gratitude for the greatest force in this world — love.
You deserve a love that makes you feel safe, secure, and seen. 🧡
Love is free 🦋
Don’t worry so much when good things leave your life. I can assure you, more good things are on their way.

Happy Sunday. Reflect on these words. Believe these words. Know that these words found you for a reason.

Whatever challenges you are experiencing right now are temporary. There is so much beauty cultivating below the surface. Move forward with faith that this universe hears you and will always take care of you.
Good things are abundant 🦋
This season is temporary. You are building a solid foundation for your blessings to blossom. 🌱
There is beauty all around you. 🌱
Release control. Stop trying to convince others to love you. Simply let their actions reveal their character. And then decide whether that’s enough for you.
Free yourself 🦋
What you deserve 🧡
This is for you 🦋
Both are important to a healthy relationship.  But many of us forget about the significance of character when we feel the magnetism of chemistry. Be mindful of the full picture.
This is for you 🦋
The quicker you let go of the wrong people; the more the right ones gravitate closer.
Let it go & live your life 🦋
Be mindful of where you’re placing your energy
Enjoy this season while it’s here. You are the only person in need of your love right now. Slow down and be present with yourself.
Be open and be free.
We cannot have true intimacy without raw vulnerability

Things are usually never as personal as they feel. If you want to work on your relationships, look inward first. Dive into yourself. Invest your energy into the things that make you feel aligned. And the rest will follow.
The strongest force in this world 💓
Happy International Women’s Day ❤️ Let us never forget our power as women.
Trust the flow of life. Trust that something is watching over you. Trust that there is a greater good in all things.
The peace you are looking for comes from within
Above all, your person should be your partner. Your best friend. Your confidant. Your safe space.
I promise you, your time will come. Enjoy this moment for all the beauty that it is.
Have patience with the process. Have faith that great things are on their way.
Enjoy this season while it’s here. There’s so much beauty in solitude. So much discovery in singleness. 🤍
A Sunday reminder that things are usually never as personal as they feel. 🤍
A Monday morning reminder. Let’s be honest with ourselves and work towards a life that is aligned with who we truly are.
Don’t be in such a rush to get rid of your pain. It’s there for a reason. It’s there to teach you. Slow down and sit with it. There’s a lot to be learned through any season of grief.

for someone that does not have the capacity to love me.

social_posts.post_text: Now repeat that to yourself, believe it in your core, and release it to the universe.
Truths I always have, and always will, live by.

A beautiful Sunday morning reminder for you. 

Yes, this is easier said than done. Integrating these beliefs and actions require intentional effort and discipline. But you are capable of that. You have power over your perspective. You can change the way you think, you can control the thought patterns you engage with. Again, it’s not going to be easy. It’s going to take time and commitment. But I promise you, the more you practice submitting to the flow of life, the easier it will become. 

You are in control. You are the master of your destiny.
It’s going to be okay. I promise you 💓
Real love nudges you to grow. Real love reflects back all the things you’ve been hiding from. And real love holds your hand through it all.
Find peace in your solitude 🤍
The hard things lead to the good things. Remind yourself of this truth through your toughest seasons.
Your Sunday morning reminder. Don’t let your anxiety fool you into thinking anything different 🤍
Don’t settle for anything less. You deserve a love that overflows, a love that reassures, a love that makes you feel seen and secure.
Trust in the process. Wait for the right moment to fall.
Let go and let it be. Everyone is on their own individual journey.
Trust yourself. Trust your intuition. Trust your gut feelings telling you to start that project, to make that phone call, to buy that plane ticket. Trust yourself.
Please remind yourself of this. Do not allow someone’s rejection of you to influence the way you see yourself. You are beautiful. And you will meet the right people who see that beauty in you.
I hope this finds everyone who needs it 🤍
Let go and enjoy. This moment is all you have.
Be with someone who wants to love you back. Be with someone who doesn’t make you question the connection. Be with someone who makes you feel safe.
Be a source of light. Be a source of life.
To know loss, is to know love. To know love, is to know loss. It’s part of the journey my friends. Don’t let your fears ruin something beautiful.

Read these words. Soak in these words. Meditate on these words. Please don’t fall for the anxious thoughts in your mind telling you that you’re not good enough. These words were meant to find you. They were meant to remind you that people really love you.
Live your life with absolute certainty that the universe is on your side. Good things happen to you. Good people are attracted to you. You don’t need to worry so much. Just enjoy this beautiful life.
The beauty of authenticity 💓 This life is so short and so beautiful. Be yourself and the right people will find you.
Be with someone who puts your soul at ease. 🧡
The best time to start is today. 🤍
Your perspective creates your reality.

Every person, every situation, every experience that you go through, is meant to shape you into the whole, embodied person that you’re destined to be. Don’t worry so much about the future. You’re exactly where you need to be.
Stop exhausting yourself trying to find answers you may simply never know. Just accept this moment for what it is, and move forward with faith that better things are around the corner.
Not everyone is forever. Appreciate people while you have them and gently let them go when it’s time to depart. 🧡
A beautiful reminder. Just because something ended doesn’t mean that it wasn’t beautiful. Some people are just transitory experiences. Enjoy them and then gently let them go.
The big gestures are great, but it’s the tiny gestures that show who someone really is. It’s the small actions when no one is paying attention that really matter.

Just because something ended doesn’t mean it wasn’t beautiful. Some people are just transitory experiences. That’s okay. Hold onto that love in your heart and trust that there is more coming towards you.
Love is free 🦋
There’s already a lot of uncertainty in this life, a lot of things outside of our control. Be with someone who makes you feel chosen. Be with someone who makes you feel seen and secure.
You deserve someone who is sure about you. My friends, there is already a lot of uncertainty in this life. You deserve someone who is sure about you.
Allow life to unfold in the way it’s supposed to. Enjoy people while you have them, and let them go when it’s time.
Never again ❤️
Both are important — but chemistry is fleeting, character is enduring
Be patient with yourself. You are learning, you are growing, you are evolving into the person you’re meant to be.
Please remember — nothing is ever as personal as it feels 🤍

Every season is only a season. Appreciate it for what it is. New seasons are coming, new growth is coming, new opportunities are on their way. Trust in this moment that there are bigger things cultivating below the surface.
True joy is found in the small moments, the in-between moments, the seemingly insignificant moments.

A beautiful reminder for you. Let it all go, let it all roll off of you. 

Yes, this is easier said than done. Integrating these beliefs and actions require intentional effort and discipline. But you are capable of that. You have power over your perspective.

You can change the way you think, you can control the thought patterns you engage with. Again, it's not going to be easy. It's going to take time and commitment. 

But I promise you, the more you practice submitting to the flow of life, the easier it will become.

You are in control. 
You are the master of your destiny.
Keep pushing forward, keep pushing through the difficult seasons. They are there to grow you into the person you’re meant to become.
The duality of love is what makes it so precious. ❤️
Have gratitude for your present moment. It’s here to prepare you for your future.
Don’t settle down until you find exactly that. Someone who makes you feel seen, safe, and secure. ❤️
This is your reminder. Don’t listen to your anxious thoughts, don’t feed into your worries. Nobody hates you. You are fine. Everything is fine. Breathe in. Breathe out.
You deserve to know where you stand with someone. You deserve clarity, consistency, and communication.
Ask yourself. Is this all really worth it? Is this really how you want to feel in a relationship? Is this really what you want?
You deserve to be loved freely and wholly. Please don’t settle for anything less. Don’t become comfortable accepting the bare minimum. You deserve it all.
A piece from my most recent book 🩷
Repeat this, meditate on it, believe it with your whole heart — and watch your life become a beautiful reflection of all your desires.
Your capacity to love others is marked by your capacity to love yourself.
And that’s perfectly okay. Don’t take it personally, don’t fight for someone that is not ready to love you. Let go and move forward. You will always find the people who are meant for you.

Good things are abundant. Good things will always come to you. Good things are always happening in your life. Don’t worry so much about something good leaving, because something new and beautiful is already on its way.

You don’t need to force anything. You don’t need to beg people to stay or to act a certain way. Instead, let people reveal themselves to you. Let their actions speak for themselves. Then decide if you have room for that in your life.
Life is about going after what you want. Life is about honoring your truth. Life is about creating the reality you want to live in.
A relationship is more than just love — it’s partnership.
Prioritize your peace 🤍
Your reminder to not take things too personally 🤍 Everyone is growing at their own pace
This is your reminder to not waste your days worrying about the future. Go outside, breathe, and relax. It’s all going to be okay.
The hard things lead to the good things 🤍

Chemistry and character are both important. However — many of us will mistakenly excuse bad character when we find good chemistry. Both need to exist. Attraction isn’t enough, chemistry isn’t enough. You need partnership, commitment, trust, loyalty. You need good character to sustain a healthy relationship.
Tag someone who needs to hear it 🩷
At the end of every path is you. 🧡
This life has as much beauty as you’re willing to recognize 🩷
Stay aligned and stay happy 💛
Repeat it, believe it, and watch it become your reality.

Power is vulnerability. Power is passion. Power is going after what you want. Power is speaking your dreams into existence. Power is caring more, loving harder, giving unconditionally. 

When your power comes from within, no one can strip you of it.
The more energy you pour into yourself, the more love you can give to this world 🩷
Love others and then let them go when the time comes. More and more beautiful people are on their way.
Love is a continuous decision that we must consciously make.

A reminder to let go of the wrong people. Regardless of how hard you fight for someone, if they are not the right person for you, your relationship will always feel like a struggle. You deserve to be loved freely, to be loved wholly. You don’t need to change anything, you don’t need to compromise your authenticity. All you need to do is find the person who loves you for who you are. And trust me, they are trying to find you too.
The loneliness will lead you towards the right people.

Don’t settle for less than you deserve. Don’t settle for maybes, for lukewarm, for half-love. Don’t settle for what you know you don’t want. 

The minute you decide you deserve more is the minute that more starts coming your way.
The best realization I ever made.
These are the hardest ones to let go of — but so much beauty is waiting around the corner
You’re human. You deserve love, and kindness, and forgiveness, and compassion. You are doing the best you can. Be easier on yourself.
There is no force stronger than love 💘

I promise you — it will happen. You deserve to be with someone who sees you, understands you, loves you, and cherishes you. You deserve genuine connection, you deserve full transparency and intimacy. You deserve to be fully yourself and wholly loved for who you are. 

I know the waiting can feel hopeless. I know the rejections, the failures, the heartbreaks can be discouraging. But just because it’s not coming right now doesn’t mean it’s not coming at all. It is coming. But the path to get there will likely look different than you think. And that’s okay. Surrender to the process, pour love into yourself, and keep believing that your person is out there, slowly making their way closer to you.
Come home to yourself 💖

image_entities.entity: never again will i shrink my capacity to love
for someone that does not have the capacity to love me.

social_posts.post_text: Read this to yourself. Read it again. And again. However many times you need it. Write it down. And read it again. You deserve peace of mind. You deserve to feel chosen. You deserve real love.
Tag someone who needs this 💘🦋

Never stop seeing the good in people. Never stop hoping for the best. Never stop believing in humanity. Never stop loving others, caring for others, opening your heart to others. 

People will disappoint you. And that’s okay. You will disappoint people as well. And that’s also okay. We are all human — trying to figure out this experience. 

Be gentle, be light, be love.
This is your sign to release 🦋

Stop trying to force people to change into the person you want them to be. Instead — allow them to be who they truly are, allow them to show up how they naturally would. And then decide if that’s really the person you want.
A reminder that nothing is ever as personal at it feels. Let it go and move forward with trust that you are exactly where you’re supposed to be 🦋
There’s so much waiting for you on the other side. Keep going.
Your happiness is waiting for you 💖

Learning to love the simple things has brought me the most joy in life. Life isn’t meant to be lived only for the weekends, only for the momentous celebrations and milestones. There is so much beauty in-between, in the every day moments, in the monotony. 

Life can be simple and beautiful. It can be both boring and profound. It’s not dependent on your situation — it’s dependent on your mindset.
Trust in someone’s actions, believe them when they show you their character.
Good things are abundant. Stop holding onto the past. Stop holding onto what could’ve been. The moment you let go of your past — you open yourself up to your future.
Be mindful where you put your energy 💖
One of my favorite pieces from my first book — ebb & flow 🦋
Love is all around you — you just have to acknowledge it 💖

People must grow at their own pace, they must blossom during their own seasons, they must learn in their own ways. 

Sometimes the best way we can help others grow is by offering them love while also giving them space to expand. Sometimes we need to let go and allow others to figure it out for themselves. Sometimes we have to step back and allow others to make their own realizations. 

Stop depleting your energy, stop wasting your time. Let go and let it be. It will all turn out the way it’s supposed to.
Never again ❤️
Nothing is ever as personal as it feels. Please remember that. 🩷
The duality of love 💖
Enjoy this moment with yourself. Enjoy this season of freedom. Sit with yourself, learn yourself, enjoy your own presence. This season will end before you know it. Enjoy it while you have it.
Trust in the process. So much is happening behind the scenes 💖

The season you’re in right now is the season you’re supposed to be in right now. Instead of fixating on the future — look around you and pay attention to the small details. Appreciate the little things. Enjoy the simplicity, the routine, the small moments of connection. Beauty is all around you, you just have to look for it.
Please don’t waste your time waiting for the wrong people. People can only meet you as deeply as they’ve met themselves. Let go and open your arms to what is truly aligned with who you are.
You can live a full life all on your own 🦋
Ask yourself honestly. Then decide what you will no longer tolerate.
Please know this. People love you, people want to be around you, people want you in their life. Don’t feed into the anxious thoughts. Don’t believe the lies. You are valued, cherished, and loved.

Focus on yourself. Focus on your own intentions. The love you pour into this world will always come back to you.

From my first book: ebb & flow

Real love isn’t going to stir up anxiety. Genuine connections aren’t going to leave you with questions. Please don’t waste your time waiting around for someone to fall in love with you. Stop hoping that maybe one day they’ll change their mind. You don’t deserve to be a second option, a last resort, or a convenience. You deserve to be loved wholeheartedly, to be pursued with passion and authenticity. 

Life is already hard enough. Don’t make it harder by chasing someone who isn’t sure about you.
Two ways to process your emotions. From my book Come Home to Yourself 💖

Please keep going, please keep believing that there’s more out there for you. I promise you, there is. I promise you things will get better. I promise the right people will find you, the right opportunities will come. This universe will always see you through to the end.

Check in with yourself and your surroundings. Are you where you want to be? How are the people around you making you feel? What actions do you need to take right now? What is your intuition telling you? What do you really want?
Who you decide to spend the rest of your life with is the biggest decision you will ever make. Please choose someone who also chooses you.

This is your life. This is your story. Stop thinking about what they want. Stop thinking about what they are going to do. You are in control. You have the power to make decisions for yourself. Please — go live your life for you.

Slow down and be intentional with your gratitude. Carve out space to reflect on all the little beautiful things in your life. Sometimes we are so concentrated on the future, that we forget to enjoy all the things we currently are blessed with. Take some time today to practice gratitude. Let it wash over you. And watch as your life becomes more vibrant and beautiful.
Allow yourself to feel the pain. Reflect on what you want to do differently. Offer yourself forgiveness. Let go and move forward. It’s all part of the process.

Love always wins in the end. Even if that means you get rejected, disappointed, or abandoned — you will still win. You will always find what is meant for you. You will always come closer to the people who will understand you. You will always win.
Learning to release will liberate you 🤍

When someone tells you they’re emotionally unavailable — please believe them. When someone tells you they’re not ready for a relationship — don’t try to force it. Love requires action. And if someone isn’t willing or ready to take action, the relationship will never work. Please spare yourself the heartache and disappointment and go find what you’re looking for. Find someone who wants the same things you want. Find someone who is ready and eager to love you. Find someone who wants to care for your heart and see you happy. This is what you deserve. And this is what you will find if you’re willing to let go and wait for the right person.

Relax, trust, and breathe. You want the things you want because they are destined for you. No one can strip you of that. However — timing is out of our control. There are bigger things at play that you can’t see. Relax and trust that you’re exactly where you’re supposed to be.

Letting go of your anxious thoughts is a practice. It’s not always easy, but I’m here you remind you, you can do it. You have the power within you. Relax your mind and ground yourself in this moment. Breathe through it. Release it and gently let go. Move on to a new activity, something that engages your brain and makes you feel peaceful. Do this as many times as you need. With practice and repetition, you will feel more in control of your anxious thoughts.

Because that’s what you deserve. You deserve peace, you deserve certainty, you deserve love, assurance, support, and consideration. That’s what you deserve.

An excerpt from my book ‘Come Home to Yourself’
5 truths I always try to live by, 5 truths I try to always remind myself.
Your reminder to find love in everything 🦋

New collection is officially live! I’ve been so excited about this 🤍 I hope this collection can be a small piece of inspiration for you all. We all need reminders that people love us, that life is going to work out perfectly, and that love surrounds us in every moment. And I hope these pieces can be that reminder for you. 

Link for purchase in bio 🦋

Let go and trust that everything is working out the way it’s supposed to. Let go and trust that nothing is ever as personal as it feels. Let go and trust that you are walking in the right direction. Let go and trust that the right people will always find their way to you.

Life is always going to be life. Inconveniences are always going to happen, bad seasons are always going to come and go. It’s up to you to create peace inside. It’s up to you to create joy throughout all of life’s circumstances.

Love is all around you — and love will always find you. Don’t worry so much, my friend. Everything’s going to be okay. Sit back and look for all the simple little loves in your life. Appreciate the small joys, all the small moments of connection.

This excerpt is from my book ‘Come Home to Yourself.’ Products are available through the link in my bio ❤️

This is your reminder: Life is going to work out perfectly. People love you. Don’t worry so much about love. 

New collection available through the link in my bio ❤️
The details define the truth. It’s so important to pay close attention to the small things people say and do. This will tell you everything you need to know.
Just because things don’t make sense right now, doesn’t mean there is no sense in it at all. Be patient, my friend. You will soon understand that everything is happening for a reason.

This is why communication & time is so important. We can’t assume people’s intentions, we can’t assume their character. We can’t assume people have the same heart, or values, or morals as we do. Pay attention to the details, ask the hard questions. It will save you a lot of time, and a lot of heartbreak.
Your Sunday reminder. Don’t worry so much, my friends. Everything is going to turn out alright 💖 You can find prints & apparel with this quote through the link in my bio <3

The biggest lie we tell ourselves is that things will naturally change without us first taking action. If we continue to engage in the same habits, hang out with the same people, stay in the same place — things will never change. If we continue to hold onto the past, fixate on the people who don’t want us, or focus on what’s comfortable and familiar — new opportunities will never come. In order to create tangible, lasting change, we must take action. We must reevaluate our habits, we must make some hard decisions. We must leave what’s comfortable and prepare ourselves for something new. Everything you want is waiting for you. You just have to go after it.
If you’re not sure what you want right now — start by asking yourself these questions. I promise you — you will find your way.

Let it go, friend. Nothing is as personal as it seems, nothing is as serious as it feels. Be easy on yourself, have compassion for your set backs. We are all on this journey together — learning, growing, and evolving together.

Not everyone is ready for a real relationship — and that’s okay. Don’t waste your time chasing people who aren’t ready for the depth of love you wish to share. I promise you — it exists, you just have to be willing to wait.
You are the love you are looking for. You are the comfort you need. Slow down and be with yourself. All the answers you are looking for are inside of you.

This is your sign to stop thinking about them and start living your life. You deserve someone who gives you consistency. You deserve someone who is sure about you. Let it go. Stop trying to find answers, stop trying to rationalize everything. Just let it go and move forward with faith that the right people will find their way to you.

Good things take time. This is your sign to not worry so much about where you are in life right now. Stop comparing your journey to everyone else’s. Everyone is on a different path, everyone has a different purpose. Trust that you are exactly where you’re supposed to be, and focus on what you can do now to get you to where you want to be.

I understand — it can be really hard to let go of beautiful connections. It’s hard to move forward when every bone in our body is aching for the past. It’s hard to open our hearts to new people when we haven’t fully let go of previous loves.

But I promise you — when you decide to finally let go, and trust that there are better things on the horizon — better things will come. They will always come. But you have to act first and let go of what’s no longer serving you.
Let yourself love. Give yourself permission to feel. The duality of love is what makes it so precious.
Step by step, little by little. Trust the process, my friend — you’re exactly where you’re supposed to be.

And I hope this message finds the right people 💘 

From my most recent book ‘Come Home to Yourself’

I wrote this years ago when I was heartbroken. I wrote this as a reminder to myself of the love that I desired, of the love that I deserved. I wrote this as a vision to hold onto, as a prophetic word to keep close to my heart. And I truly believed it, I trusted that my person was somewhere out there in the world. Even when I experienced further heartbreak, even when the same disappointing relationship patterns continued to appear — I believed that one day I would meet someone who gets it. 

And I can tell you now, with certainty — I was right.

I hope you can hold onto this vision too. ❤️

I know you may think —  this is much easier said than done. And you’re right. It’s not easy to just stop overthinking, it’s not easy to just let it all go. But — it is possible. You are in control, even when you feel powerless. You have the autonomy to create a new day tomorrow, a day different than today or yesterday. Power is infinite, it is all around you. Start with the small things, and the small things will eventually lead you toward the big things.

Yesterday I posted a question box on my story and received a lot of responses regarding love & romantic relationships. While I work on responding to all your lovely questions, I think this is an incredibly important message to sink into. 

Choose someone with good character. Choose someone who treats you with kindness and respect. Choose someone who supports you, who makes your life easier. If being with your partner feels like a continual cycle of pain, and suffering, and heartbreak — that is a clear indication that you are not where you’re supposed to be. 

When I’ve posted this message previously, I typically get a handful of comments critiquing this message, arguing that chemistry is also important. And I agree. Chemistry is incredibly important for a romantic relationship, in fact, it is necessary. However, the sentiment here is not to disregard chemistry, but rather, to not get lost in it. Oftentimes, when we feel a magnetic connection with someone, we will cling onto the relationship even when there are obvious red flags. We will mistakenly believe that because we feel such strong chemistry, this person must be our soulmate. 

But the truth is — your soulmate isn’t going to make you question your worth. Your soulmate isn’t going to ignore you, insult you, or abuse you. Your soulmate isn’t going to leave you worrying about the status of your relationship. That is not your soulmate. 

When we are evaluating a potential relationship — yes, we need to have chemistry with that person. But more importantly, we need to evaluate their character. We need to understand their values, their morals, their capacity to love and support others. This is what will sustain the relationship. 

This will build a healthy foundation for true love to blossom.

You deserve a consistent love. And I promise you — it does exist. You deserve to live a life where you feel loved every day, where you feel cherished in every moment. You deserve to wake up in the morning with the peace of mind that your partner desires you. You deserve to go to bed at night with the clarity that you are exactly where you’re supposed to be. 

I promise you my friends — it does exist — but you have to create room for it. You have to stop settling for less, you have to stop staying in spaces where you are not valued. You must decide that you want more for yourself. You must decide that the time to start making change is today. 

An excerpt from my book: Come Home to Yourself

Letting go is hard. Especially when you’re letting go of someone you thought you would have a forever with. Especially when you’re letting go of someone you had a beautifully, intense connection with. I understand. But what you must remind yourself is that there are so many other beautifully intense connections still waiting for you — each one uniquely different. 

Yes — you will never find the exact same love again. But consider that a good thing. Think of all the beautiful new types of love that you can experience, the new dynamics that you didn’t even know existed. 

I promise you — you will find love again. Heartbreak and loss is an inevitable part of the human experience. Give yourself time to grieve, give yourself time to grow. And please, remind yourself that there is more love out there for you. This isn’t the end, it’s the beginning. 💘

You are exactly who you’re supposed to be. Please don’t change yourself for anyone. The right people will always find you. 

An excerpt from my first book ‘ebb & flow’ 🤎
Life is a constant cycle of learning and growing. Be sure to take moments to reflect on what you’ve learned, how you’ve grown, and what you want for the next season of life.

If you continue to hang out with people who drain your energy, who criticize everything you do, who make you feel small and unworthy — you will have an extremely difficult time growing into the person you want to become. 

Your external environment has so much impact on your ability to evolve. And sometimes that evolution requires a reevaluation of the people, habits, and spaces we are engaging with.

Learning to fall in love with your life, regardless of your current situation, is the greatest act of self-love you could ever make. 

As humans, we often think that love, happiness, fulfillment, and all the like, are waiting for us on the other side. We mistakenly believe that in order to feel good feelings, something good needs to happen first. We think we need to get the new job, we need to find the right relationship, we need to move to the bigger home — before we can feel satisfied. But that’s just not true. Love isn’t waiting for you in the future. Joy is not at the will of the world. 

It’s here, and it’s now, and it’s embedded in every moment — you just have to open your eyes to it. You have to give yourself permission to feel those feelings, despite what is or isn’t happening. 

Life is unpredictable and uncertain. If we give away all our power to our external circumstances, we will never feel the peace of true joy.

Trying to force someone to become the person you want is unnatural. It’s exhausting for both parties. Instead, allow people to show up as who they really are. Allow their actions to speak for themselves. And then make a decision about whether or not this is what you want. 

However — it’s important to understand that communicating your needs, desires, and preferences is still very important. We can’t read minds, many of us don’t intuitively know what our partner wants. There is a learning curve to love — and you need someone that is willing to learn to love you in the ways you want to be loved.

However — if those desires and needs are consistently not met, or consistently disregarded — please don’t exhaust yourself trying to force this person to change. Instead, shift your energy inward and make a decision that prioritizes your needs and well-being. 

From my second book: Come Home to Yourself

This is a really tough realization. The realization that sometimes, the best thing you can do for the person you love is to let them go, to allow them to learn and grow at their own pace. 

All people are shaped and curved by their own individual experiences. And based on those experiences, people create their values, their beliefs, their preferences and their personal narratives. There is no right way or wrong way. Every individual has their own truth. And it’s their responsibility to discover and uncover that truth.

We cannot force it upon them. We can’t force others to do things the way we think is right. We can’t force people to grow at the pace or in the direction that we want them to. We must let go of control. We must send them love and wish them well — and continue on our own journey of discovery.

This is the best thing we can do for the people we love. Give them love, and give them space to evolve.

Stop seeking approval from people who will never understand you. They can’t understand you. And you should take that as a compliment. 

From my first book: ebb & flow 🤎
You are worthy of a full, passionate, reciprocal, consistent, complete type of love. Please do not trick yourself into thinking otherwise. You’re not needy — you just need to find the right person.

The pain of heartbreak is very real. The fear of letting go and not knowing what comes next is very isolating. But all of those things — pain, fear, isolation — are also transformative. They are catalysts of change, indicators that a new and beautiful path is waiting for us. 

Yes — feel your heartbreak, let yourself cry, allow yourself to process those heavy emotions. But don’t let those emotions define who you are. Use those emotions to define who you want to become. 

Use the pain to dig deeper into yourself, to release the trauma that you’ve been storing up all these years. Use the fear to catapult you onto a different path, to become a renewed version of yourself. Use the isolation to discover who you really are, what you really want, and what you really love. 

Heartbreak isn’t just the end of something beautiful; it’s the beginning of something unknown.

I wrote this to myself about two years ago during a season of life that was filled with uncertainty. I wasn’t sure where I was going to live next, when my next paycheck would come, what direction my career was going to go in, or if I would ever find my person. And the more I found myself worrying about those things, the more I realized how deeply I needed to let go. I was paralyzed by my fear and my worry — I was creatively blocked, I was intuitively blocked, I was unable to make conscious decisions for myself because my head was so clouded by everything I was choosing to worry about. I had no energy left to give towards my life because I wasted it all on my anxieties.

I wrote this as a love letter to myself — a string of affirmations to ground myself in when I felt my anxieties creeping up. To this day, I still read these words to myself in times of uncertainty. 

These words aren’t grounded in toxic positivity or a naive belief that everything always goes the way you want it to. Because oftentimes, it doesn’t. These words are a reminder to let go. To let life happen to you, rather than trying to control it. Your worry and your fear aren’t going to change your circumstances. But you know what will? Letting go. Trusting your gut. Believing in miracles. Having hope. Practicing gratitude. Writing down lists of your own affirmations. That will radically change your life. 

Two years later and I can say with confidence that my life has worked out perfectly. Not always in the ways I thought it would; but I wouldn’t have it any other way. 

If you’re reading this — I love you. Everything is going to be okay.

Just one small act of letting go every day will add up over time. Just one small moment of shifting your energy elsewhere every day will make a difference. Just one small decision to focus on the positive every day will transform your inner world. Give it a try.

The truth is — if someone is being inconsistent with you, if someone is ignoring your texts, if someone is giving you minimal effort — that is a clear indication that they don’t value you or don’t want to be committed to you. Someone who truly values you would never put your relationship in jeopardy by making you feel unimportant. That’s the bare minimum and you deserve that. 

But if you still find yourself in a place of questioning, over-analyzing, and second-guessing — give yourself peace and just ask them. Be straight forward with your feelings. Be honest about what you feel and what you want. And ask if they feel the same, ask if they want the same things as you. Sure — you might get rejected.  But that’s okay. Rejection isn’t a bad thing — it saves you time and gives you peace in the long run. Knowing the truth WILL set you free. You will become that much closer to meeting the person who will value you and prioritize you. 

And when you have these conversations — have them with discernment. Unfortunately— not everyone is truthful in these moments. So use your best judgement. Trust your gut. If what they’re saying isn’t aligning with their actions — then be careful. Proceed with caution and be mindful of how this person is making you feel. 

My friends — you deserve to feel valued and loved and safe. You deserve it all. Set yourself free.

You don’t need to have a grand or extraordinary life to fall in love with it. The most beautiful things are actually quite simple — love, laughter, language, a big hug, a warm cup of tea, a pretty sunset, a smiling baby, a home cooked meal, a good book, a sunny day, a rainstorm, an ordinary day spent relaxing in your home. The more you pay attention to these simple moments of joy, the more you’ll realize how beautiful your life really is. 

Book: “Come Home to Yourself”

I think everyone needs this reminder from time to time. When life gets busy and we don’t have time to ground ourselves in truth, it’s easy to become disillusioned by our deepest fears and anxieties. We will mistakenly believe that the people close to us don’t love us, we will overthink every interaction we have and question whether we did something wrong. None of that is true my friend. It’s just your anxiety lying to you. 

And that’s why it’s so important to develop a habit of grounding yourself in truth. And that practice will look different for every person. That may mean regular exercise, meditation, writing, reading, going outside, dancing, singing, laughing, or spending time alone. Whatever it is — make sure you’re cutting out time for yourself; especially during these busy times of the year. 

When life gets busy, our minds get busy too, and it can become more difficult to discern the truth.

But today I am here to tell you — people love you.

If you don’t know what you want to do with your life — start by reflecting on some of these questions. Be honest with yourself and don’t allow your anxieties, fears, or perceived limitations to get in the way. What is your most uninhibited dream? Your answers will lead you in the right direction. 

Book: Come Home to Yourself 💖

Sometimes we think we need closure to move on, but the truth is, there are some people who will never be able to give us the closure we are seeking. There are some people incapable of communicating what went wrong, some people who would rather run away than make amends. Please don’t exhaust yourself trying to force closure out of these individuals. Nothing they say will ever make you feel better. 

You’re in control. Give yourself the closure you are looking for and move forward.

Please do it. Go for it. Pursue that passion, write that book, start that business, take that jump. You’re thinking about it for a reason, you desire it because it’s meant for you. Trust your gut and go for it.

Be kind. Be loving. Be gentle. Be forgiving. Be understanding. Be patient. Be sweet. 
But at the same time — Be firm. Be strong. Be accountable. Be independent. Be self-assured. Be confident. Be unafraid. Be secure. Be powerful. 

Love others in a way that does not make you sacrifice your love for yourself.

Life is hard enough — be kind to yourself today. 

Book: Come Home to Yourself

If you’re currently in a hard season of life — please know there are much better days on the other side. The hard seasons are there to teach you, grow you, and show you who you’re meant to become. Keep moving forward — the good things are coming closer.

A thought for the day — let your mind rest, try your best to let go of your anxieties throughout the day. I know it’s hard, I know it’s easier said than done. But you are still in control. Small actions everyday will add up. Small moments of breakthrough will lead to huge transformations. 

Book: Come Home to Yourself

Your peace & well-being should be your highest priority.  If something, or someone, consistently interferes with that, it’s your responsibility to reconsider your priorities. Think about what you really want. Think about how you want to feel. Think about what you deserve. And don’t settle for anything less.

Don’t ignore that voice inside you. It’s there for a reason — it’s there to guide you through your purpose. Don’t ignore your intuition, don’t feed into your doubts. You don’t need to have all the answers, you don’t need to figure it all out right now. Just take one step at a time, one step in the right direction, one step in sync with your inner guidance.
You exist. You are the exact person someone in this world has been waiting for. And if someone else’s dream person exists — why can’t yours exist too?

Please share your story with the world, share your art with the world, share your passions with the world. There are so many people who will be blessed by it — and you will be blessed just through the process of sharing your heart with others.

This is a big & beautiful lesson. Many of us mistakenly believe that happiness is somewhere in the future waiting for us. That once we get the job, the relationship, the promotion, the house, the car, the acceptance letter — the happiness will suddenly wash over us. And maybe it will — but only for a fleeting moment. 

Real, true, deep, and enduring happiness must be created from within. Happiness is not a momentary thing, it’s not a momentous event — it’s an everyday practice. It’s an everyday commitment to live a life that feels good to you. It’s a promise to stay aligned with yourself, to make time for the things that give you joy, to hold yourself accountable in your daily schedule.

The small, everyday things are actually the most beautiful. The mundane, the simplicity, the routine, the comfort. Remind yourself how lucky you are to be able to engage in your everyday joys. Remind yourself how lucky you are to be alive.
It’s all happening for a reason. It’s all part of the process. Don’t lose trust, don’t lose hope. The right people are going to find you. I promise.
Please know this. Please believe this. It will happen for you, it will happen for you again. There is always more love, more connection, more experiences. Please trust this.

Be honest with yourself. What is it that you really want? Do you want this? Are you happy? Are you fulfilled? Do you feel loved? Do you feel valued? Do you feel seen? Understood? Appreciated? 

If you were to feel this way the rest of your life — what kind of life would you have? If nothing about this person were to ever change — how happy would you feel? 

The decisions you make now are the most important for the person you will one day be. Take care of your heart. Be honest with yourself. You deserve to feel loved.
You don’t really need to complicate life — the simple things will bring you all the fulfillment you’re looking for 💖

I know it’s easier said than done — but that doesn’t mean it’s impossible to do. Make a promise to yourself to try a little harder to let go throughout this next week. To worry a little less, to trust a little more. Real progress is slow progress.

Sometimes we fool ourselves into thinking that any type of love is better than the absence of love. So we make excuses for half-loves, we open our arms to half-efforts, we pretend that we’re satisfied with half-commitments. But all this does is leave us feeling even more lonely, even more isolated. If you don’t want half-love — stop settling for it. Stop convincing yourself that this is “good enough.” Stop saying yes when you want to say no. Stop hiding your true feelings, stop swallowing your honest words. 

You deserve to have real love and connection. You deserve to feel true intimacy. You deserve all your desires.
When you learn to fall in love with your life from the inside, you discover what the true purpose of life really is. To enjoy it.
Allow people to blossom in their own timing. Allow people to learn at their own pace. If they’re not in alignment with you right now — then keep moving forward. The right people will always find you.

Stop waiting for them to come around, stop secretly hoping that they’ll change their mind. You deserve to be someone’s first choice, their top priority, their best friend. You deserve to be loved freely.

You deserve to be treated with care, with consideration, with compassion, and commitment. You deserve to feel like the best version of yourself when you’re with your partner. You deserve to feel safe & secure, to feel seen & understood. It’s never too late, my friend. It’s never too late to create change in your life.

Something to remember this holiday season. Just because someone may not be by your side this year, doesn’t mean their memory or their meaning in your life needs to be forgotten. Some people are just here for seasons. Allow them to flow in & out. Be open to whatever is coming next. ❤️
The right person will make you feel loved, worthy, cherished, and respected. Please wait for the right person.
Some lessons I’ll be taking with me into the new year 💘
I’m claiming this for you in the new year. I’m praying that you will finally meet the person you have been waiting for.
Manifesting this for 2024. Believe it, meditate on it, pray over it. Life is going to work out perfectly.
Prioritize your peace in 2024. Put your mental, emotional, and physical well-being at the top of your priority list — and watch yourself evolve & transform.

You deserve someone who has the capacity to love you to the lengths that you will love them. You deserve romance, reciprocity, and reverence. You deserve to feel the true power of love — the kind of love that awakens you and expands you. You deserve a consistent love.
The best time to start your self-love journey is today.

The key to growth is finding a balance between accountability and compassion. You must own up to your self-sabotaging patterns while also offering yourself forgiveness. You must take continual steps toward changing your negative behaviors while also having patience with the process. This is how you grow, this is how you evolve.

Live your life with the certainty that it’s going to work out the way you want it to. Even if it’s not coming right now — that doesn’t mean it’s not coming in the future. Live your life with the certainty that the things you want will always come to you.
